==English==

===Etymology===
Originally a [[Roman]] building used as a [[courthouse]] or [[assembly]] [[hall]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{architecture}} A [[Christian]] [[church]] [[building]] having a [[nave]] with a [[semicircular]] [[apse]], side [[aisle]]s, a [[narthex]] and a [[clerestory]].
# A Roman Catholic church or cathedral with basilican status.

